title: Ireland
excerpt: An island nation in Western Europe
text: Ireland is an island nation in Western Europe, consisting of the Irish Free State (independent) and the island of Ireland. Dublin, the capital, is known for its Georgian architecture, literary heritage, and vibrant culture. Ireland has a population of about 5.2 million and is known for its literature, music, and pubs. The Cliffs of Moher are one of Ireland's most visited natural attractions. Ireland joined the European Union in 1973 and adopted the Euro in 2002. The country is known for its contributions to literature with famous writers like James Joyce and Samuel Beckett. Ireland is known for its strong tradition of storytelling, music, and traditional Irish dancing.
